&lt;p&gt;As you know (if not, probably the following lines gives you an idea), &lt;strong&gt;vIPer&lt;/strong&gt; was originally designed to export from &lt;em&gt;ipynb&lt;/em&gt; files to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a plain static html &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a slideshow powered by Landslide&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the last release, &lt;strong&gt;IPython&lt;/strong&gt; support this kind of exportation using the well designed and easily extensible &lt;code&gt;IPython.nbconvert&lt;/code&gt; library. Now, it is easier to incorporate the IPython machinery inside vIPer and support the exportation to several formats.
